    define('%calledVariable$s', 'foo');

There are a few possibilities
    - Maybe It's just a typo, you can check all the defined constants
      with `get_defined_constants()`
    - This constant does not exist in this scope (is it in a namespace ?)
    - You forgot a $ sign in front of a variable name: $%calledVariable$s
    - You forgot simple quotes around a string: '%calledVariable$s'

Read more about constants:
    Constant names are case-sensitive, always uppercase by convention.
    https://www.php.net/manual/en/language.constants.php
